Kelly,
I believe there is a Salvador Dali museum close by:
http://www.salvadordalimuseum.org
I missed out on it when we went to St. Pete Beach a few years ago...I
was with my mom and kids and we hadn't rented a car.

We're going to Florida for our annual vacation that first weekend +
of March also since I'm due w/baby #6 in July (I think I saw your
name on another list?). It's DH's and DS's dream vacation...spring
training in Clearwater/Sarasota, and then for more family-oriented
stuff down in the Everglades. I'm really looking forward to it, esp.
the warmer weather!

Enjoy!

Valerie in OH

messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] Tampa/St Pete?
messages.msgSnippet: Clearwater Beach is a nice spot. The beach itself is lovely and fairly unpopulated. Sand Key is just up (or down?) the road, a great place for shelling,
messages.messageBody:
Clearwater Beach is a nice spot. The beach itself is lovely and fairly unpopulated. Sand Key is just up (or down?) the road, a great place for shelling, especially sand dollars. There is a bird sanctuary that we found fasinating. There used to be a steel drum band at the big hotel at the south end of the beach....but that was a few years ago.
Hope you have a lovely trip!
melanie
